commit.message: Fix dead code detection wrt. Raise statement

Do not clean lookup list too early

The name lookup is done in two steps: first we build the lookup list,
second we perform the lookup, walking the list.

While building the lookup list, we may find an invalid situation that we
need to report. Yet this situation may not happen if the lookup is
successful before we reach the invalid situation.

Take this scenario into account while performing the lookup.

Fix #57

Upgrade github action

- Specific setup for py2.7 has gh support is now discontinued
- Upgrade dependency version
Remove spurious whitespaces

Make tests compatible with pytest

Fix #56
Require setuptools in testing for py3.12-dev

Get rid of RuntimeWarning: 'beniget.beniget' found in sys.modules after import of package 'beniget'...

Use the adequate __main__.py file to store beniget command line
interface.

As a result one should now invoke beniget through `python -m beniget file.py`

Add support for PEP 563

This PR adds support for PEP 563: Postponed Evaluation of Annotations [0]

It does so by special-parsing future imports and eventually computing
annotations, using the same evaluation strategy as pyright.

Fixes #42.

[0]: https://peps.python.org/pep-0563/

Introduce Def.islive

If True: definition might reach the final block of the scope.
If False: it's always overridden.
Add a test

When we hit a wildcard import, the wildcard def is added to the definitions of "*" and does not replace it anymore. This change ensure that beniget produces an over-approximation of the code and not an under-approxiamtion.

[ci] update worker image

Fix py27 test as a side effect.
Update the way we check for locally unbound variables

Do not add method name to local scope

fix #49
Fix scoping rule for comprehensions

Code cleaning

Remove useless assignments, unused default value etc

Rework scope handling, esp. wrt class

This was a big hole in beniget, thanks to @tristanlatr for spotting this.
